## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and may not capture all nuances of vaccine hesitancy. The rapidly evolving nature of the COVID-19 pandemic means that public perceptions and reasons for vaccine hesitancy can change over time. Additionally, the focus on U.S.-based sources may not fully represent global perspectives on vaccine hesitancy. Further research is needed to explore these issues in different cultural and geographical contexts.